{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Change the law so that Independent Trusts are regulated",
        "additional_details": "I have recently discovered that where life assurance lump sums go into a discretionary trust, the Independent Trusts involved are not regulated and solely operate on their own internal policies. This means that where a discrepancy arises, they only have their own internal complaints procedure to follow, which I have discovered is not fit for purpose. They can essentially do whatever they like, and there\u2019s nothing anyone can do about it. They should be regulated, and answerable to a higher body.",
        "background": "I would like the government to ensure that all Independent Trusts are regulated by the same legal framework, and overseen by a specific legal authority or government approved regulator.",
